33namespace webrtc {
34
35typedef rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpTransceiverProxyWithInternal<RtpTransceiver>>
36 RtpTransceiverProxyRefPtr;
37
38// Captures partial state to be used for rollback. Applicable only in
39// Unified Plan.
40class TransceiverStableState {
41 public:
42 TransceiverStableState() {}
43 void set_newly_created();
44 void SetMSectionIfUnset(absl::optional<std::string> mid,
45 absl::optional<size_t> mline_index);
46 void SetRemoteStreamIdsIfUnset(const std::vector<std::string>& ids);
47 void SetInitSendEncodings(
48 const std::vector<RtpEncodingParameters>& encodings);
49 absl::optional<std::string> mid() const { return mid_; }
50 absl::optional<size_t> mline_index() const { return mline_index_; }
51 absl::optional<std::vector<std::string>> remote_stream_ids() const {
52 return remote_stream_ids_;
53 }
54 absl::optional<std::vector<RtpEncodingParameters>> init_send_encodings()
55 const {
56 return init_send_encodings_;
57 }
58 bool has_m_section() const { return has_m_section_; }
59 bool newly_created() const { return newly_created_; }
60
61 private:
62 absl::optional<std::string> mid_;
63 absl::optional<size_t> mline_index_;
64 absl::optional<std::vector<std::string>> remote_stream_ids_;
65 absl::optional<std::vector<RtpEncodingParameters>> init_send_encodings_;
66 // Indicates that mid value from stable state has been captured and
67 // that rollback has to restore the transceiver. Also protects against
68 // subsequent overwrites.
69 bool has_m_section_ = false;
70 // Indicates that the transceiver was created as part of applying a
71 // description to track potential need for removing transceiver during
72 // rollback.
73 bool newly_created_ = false;
74};
75
76// This class encapsulates the active list of transceivers on a
77// PeerConnection, and offers convenient functions on that list.
78// It is a single-thread class; all operations must be performed
79// on the same thread.
80class TransceiverList {
81 public:
82 // Returns a copy of the currently active list of transceivers. The
83 // list consists of rtc::scoped_refptrs, which will keep the transceivers
84 // from being deallocated, even if they are removed from the TransceiverList.
85 std::vector<RtpTransceiverProxyRefPtr> List() const {
86 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&sequence_checker_);
87 return transceivers_;
88 }
89 // As above, but does not check thread ownership. Unsafe.
90 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/12692): Refactor and remove
91 std::vector<RtpTransceiverProxyRefPtr> UnsafeList() const {
92 return transceivers_;
93 }
94
95 // Returns a list of the internal() pointers of the currently active list
96 // of transceivers. These raw pointers are not thread-safe, so need to
97 // be consumed on the same thread.
98 std::vector<RtpTransceiver*> ListInternal() const;
99
100 void Add(RtpTransceiverProxyRefPtr transceiver) {
101 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&sequence_checker_);
102 transceivers_.push_back(transceiver);
103 }
104 void Remove(RtpTransceiverProxyRefPtr transceiver) {
105 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&sequence_checker_);
106 transceivers_.erase(
107 std::remove(transceivers_.begin(), transceivers_.end(), transceiver),
108 transceivers_.end());
109 }
110 RtpTransceiverProxyRefPtr FindBySender(
111 rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpSenderInterface> sender) const;
112 RtpTransceiverProxyRefPtr FindByMid(const std::string& mid) const;
113 RtpTransceiverProxyRefPtr FindByMLineIndex(size_t mline_index) const;
114
115 // Find or create the stable state for a transceiver.
116 TransceiverStableState* StableState(RtpTransceiverProxyRefPtr transceiver) {
117 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&sequence_checker_);
118 return &(transceiver_stable_states_by_transceivers_[transceiver]);
119 }
120
121 void DiscardStableStates() {
122 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&sequence_checker_);
123 transceiver_stable_states_by_transceivers_.clear();
124 }
125
126 std::map<RtpTransceiverProxyRefPtr, TransceiverStableState>& StableStates() {
127 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&sequence_checker_);
128 return transceiver_stable_states_by_transceivers_;
129 }
130
131 private:
132 RTC_NO_UNIQUE_ADDRESS SequenceChecker sequence_checker_;
133 std::vector<RtpTransceiverProxyRefPtr> transceivers_;
134 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/12692): Add RTC_GUARDED_BY(sequence_checker_);
135
136 // Holds changes made to transceivers during applying descriptors for
137 // potential rollback. Gets cleared once signaling state goes to stable.
138 std::map<RtpTransceiverProxyRefPtr, TransceiverStableState>
139 transceiver_stable_states_by_transceivers_
140 RTC_GUARDED_BY(sequence_checker_);
141 // Holds remote stream ids for transceivers from stable state.
142 std::map<RtpTransceiverProxyRefPtr, std::vector<std::string>>
143 remote_stream_ids_by_transceivers_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(sequence_checker_);
144};
